casebody.data:
No. 366, No. 831,

Misc.

Misc.

Devaney v. Cochran, Director, Division of Corrections of Florida; and Byrd v. Warden, Maryland House of Correction. Petitioners pro se. Richard W. Ervin, Attorney General of Florida, and B. Clarke Nichols, Assistant Attorney General, for respondent in No. 366, Mise.

Motions for leave to file petitions for writs of habeas corpus denied. Treating the papers submitted as petitions for writs of certiorari, certiorari is denied.

Reported below: No. 831, Mise., 222 Md. 597, 158 A. 2d 120.
